    "narrative": {
        "business_description": "A.O. Smith Corp. is a leading manufacturer of residential and commercial water heaters, boilers, and water treatment products. Has two reportable segments: North America (76% of ’24 sales); and Rest of World (24%), which primarily serves China, Europe, and India. Brands include A.O. Smith, GSW, Lochinvar, Reliance, and Takagi. As of 12/31/24, had approx. 12,700 employees and 28 wholly-owned and leased manufacturing facilities. Smith Family Voting Trust owns 96.9% of Class A shares; Officers & directors, 1.7% of regular common; Vanguard Group, 11.6% (2/25 proxy). CEO: Stephen Shafer. Chair.: Kevin Wheeler. Incorporated: Delaware. Address: 11270 West Park Place, Milwaukee, WI 53224. Telephone: 414-359-4130. Internet: www.aosmith.com.",
        "commentary_highlights": [
            {
                "topic": "Acquisition",
                "text": "Company agreed to acquire privately held Leonard Valve Company (LVC) for approx. $412 million (cash upfront $470 million net of $58 million related tax benefits). LVC expected adjusted EBITDA nearly $35 million in 2026."
            },
            {
                "topic": "Strategic review / China exposure",
                "text": "Management strategic review could result in selling all or part of China operations; China represented about $760 million (~20%) of 2024 dollar-denominated sales; China sales expected to decline 10% in 2025 after a 6% local-currency drop the prior year."
            },
            {
                "topic": "Demand mix",
                "text": "U.S. replacement/retrofit market is major driver: ~80–85% of water heater/boiler sales from existing buildings vs 15–20% from new construction."
            },
            {
                "topic": "Timeliness context",
                "text": "Shares no longer stand out for year-ahead price performance (Timeliness 3, Average), but LVC acquisition and potential China exit could be catalysts."
            }
        ],
        "footnotes": {
            "eps_adjustments": "EPS excludes nonrecurring gain/(losses): ’10, ($0.47); ’12, $0.38; ’14, ($0.15); ’18, ($0.03); ’22, (1.60). Also excludes discontinued operations: ’10, $1.18; ’11, $4.18; ’12, ($0.08). Next earnings report due early February.",
            "dividends_timing": "Dividends historically paid mid-February, May, August & November; dividend reinvestment plan available.",
            "intangibles_note": "Includes intangible assets: In 2024: $1082.8 mill., $7.50/sh.",
